## Test Maintainability Assessment

**Overall: This is a clean, well-structured test class.** You're already doing several things right — factory method with optional parameters, parameterized tests with `DisplayName`, clear AAA structure, and good test isolation. Only minor findings below.

---

### Finding 1: Repeated magic literals (3 occurrences)

`"user@example.com", "admin"` appears identically in 3 non-parameterized tests:

```csharp
// GenerateToken_ExpiredCredentials_ThrowsAuthException
service.GenerateToken("user@example.com", "admin");

// RevokeToken_ValidToken_MarksRevoked
service.GenerateToken("user@example.com", "admin");

// RevokeToken_AlreadyRevoked_IsIdempotent
service.GenerateToken("user@example.com", "admin");
```

**Suggested refactoring** — extend the existing factory to return a token too:

```csharp
private static (TokenService Service, Token Token) CreateServiceWithToken(
    TimeSpan? clockOffset = null)
{
    var service = CreateTokenService(clockOffset);
    var token = service.GenerateToken("user@example.com", "admin");
    return (service, token);
}
```

The revoke tests then become:

```csharp
var (service, token) = CreateServiceWithToken();
service.RevokeToken(token.Id);
Assert.IsTrue(service.IsRevoked(token.Id));
```

**Trade-off:** Reduces three call sites to one definition, but adds a layer of indirection. Worth it here since the email/role are irrelevant to what the revoke tests verify — they're just noise.

---

### What's already good

| Practice | Status |
|---|---|
| Factory method (`CreateTokenService`) with optional params | ✅ Already extracted |
| Parameterized tests with `[DataRow]` + `DisplayName` | ✅ Well applied |
| AAA structure | ✅ Clear in every test |
| Test isolation (no shared mutable state) | ✅ Each test is independent |
| Idempotency edge case covered | ✅ Good coverage instinct |

---

### Refactoring priority

| # | Finding | Occurrences | Risk | Recommendation |
|---|---------|-------------|------|----------------|
| 1 | Repeated `GenerateToken` call with identical args | 3 | Low | Extract helper — **optional but tidy** |

**Bottom line:** This suite is in good shape. The one minor cleanup above would reduce noise in the revoke tests, but it's a preference call rather than a pressing need. No high-priority maintainability issues found.
